name: at
summary: Identical to . Returns the item at a given index, allowing for positive and negative integers. Negative integers count back from the last item in the collection.

name: clone
summary: Creates an identical shallow copy of this collection.

name: combineEntries
summary: Creates a Collection from a list of entries.

name: concat
summary: Combines this collection with others into a new collection. None of the source collections are modified.

name: difference
summary: The difference method returns a new structure containing items where the key is present in one of the original structures but not the other.

name: each
summary: Identical to , but returns the collection instead of undefined.

name: ensure
summary: Obtains the value of the given key if it exists, otherwise sets and returns the value provided by the default value generator.

name: equals
summary: Checks if this collection shares identical items with another. This is different to checking for equality using equal-signs, because the collections may be different objects, but contain the same data.

name: every
summary: Checks if all items passes a test. Identical in behavior to .

name: filter
summary: Identical to , but returns a Collection instead of an Array.

name: find
summary: Searches for a single item where the given function returns a truthy value. This behaves like . All collections used in Discord.js are mapped using their id property, and if you want to find by id you should use the get method. See  for details.

name: findKey
summary: Searches for the key of a single item where the given function returns a truthy value. This behaves like , but returns the key rather than the positional index.

name: first
summary: Obtains the first value(s) in this collection.

name: firstKey
summary: Obtains the first key(s) in this collection.

name: flatMap
summary: Maps each item into a Collection, then joins the results into a single Collection. Identical in behavior to .

name: hasAll
summary: Checks if all of the elements exist in the collection.

name: hasAny
summary: Checks if any of the elements exist in the collection.

name: intersect
summary: The intersect method returns a new structure containing items where the keys and values are present in both original structures.

name: keyAt
summary: Identical to . Returns the key at a given index, allowing for positive and negative integers. Negative integers count back from the last item in the collection.

name: last
summary: Obtains the last value(s) in this collection.

name: lastKey
summary: Obtains the last key(s) in this collection.

name: map
summary: Maps each item to another value into an array. Identical in behavior to .

name: mapValues
summary: Maps each item to another value into a collection. Identical in behavior to .

name: merge
summary: Merges two Collections together into a new Collection.

name: partition
summary: Partitions the collection into two collections where the first collection contains the items that passed and the second contains the items that failed.

name: random
summary: Obtains unique random value(s) from this collection.

name: randomKey
summary: Obtains unique random key(s) from this collection.

name: reduce
summary: Applies a function to produce a single value. Identical in behavior to .

name: reverse
summary: Identical to  but returns a Collection instead of an Array.

name: some
summary: Checks if there exists an item that passes a test. Identical in behavior to .

name: sort
summary: The sort method sorts the items of a collection in place and returns it. The sort is not necessarily stable in Node 10 or older. The default sort order is according to string Unicode code points.

name: sorted
summary: The sorted method sorts the items of a collection and returns it. The sort is not necessarily stable in Node 10 or older. The default sort order is according to string Unicode code points.

name: sweep
summary: Removes items that satisfy the provided filter function.

name: tap
summary: Runs a function on the collection and returns the collection.

name: Collection
summary: A Map with additional utility methods. This is used throughout discord.js rather than Arrays for anything that has an ID, for significantly improved performance and ease-of-use.

name: ReadonlyCollection
summary: Represents an immutable version of a collection
